<!DOCTYPE recipe [<!ELEMENT recipe ((title?,details?,ingredients, instructions?,cuisine) | (title?,cuisine,details?,ingredients, instructions?))><!ELEMENT title (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT cuisine (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT ingredients (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT instructions (#PCDATA)><!ELEMENT details (#PCDATA)>]>
<recipe>
<title>
Grape Salad
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 10 minutes
COURSE: Dessert
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: grapes, salad
SERVINGS: 12
</details>
<ingredients>
4 lbs . red or green seedless grapes or a combination of the two
8 oz . plain non-fat Greek yogurt
8 oz . reduced-fat cream cheese softened
1/4 c . granulated sugar
1 tsp . vanilla
1/4 c . brown sugar packed
1/4 c . chopped pecans
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Wash grapes, and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix yogurt, cream cheese, granulated sugar, and vanilla together.
Fold in grapes.
Sprinkle brown sugar and pecans on top.
Serve immediately, or cover and chill until ready to use.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>